lem, persuade them to seek assistance, and encourage them to adjust to and use hearing aids.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aDeafnessvPopular works. 0aHearing aids. 0aHearing disordersvPopular works. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Hearing & Speech.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300130287423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300130287.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO